  "texts": [
    "The authors highlighted a previous approach which applied Gabor-filter to minimize noise.",
    "Though, the approach created a scenario of having crack images detected to be larger in size than their true image size (shape).",
    "This necessitated the new proposed approach that considers crack detection without pre-processing aimed at reducing noise using a clustering algorithm.",
    "Images were categorized to classes with little noise components having two classes.",
    "While, those with higher noise components with three classes."
